The designation of "(2R)" indicates the stereochemical configuration of the molecule, specifically the arrangement of the substituents around the chiral center at the 2-position of the pentane backbone. The nomenclature further specifies the presence of an ethyl group attached to the nitrogen atom, as well as three methyl groups attached to the carbon atoms in positions 3, 3, and 2 of the pentane chain. By understanding the molecular formula of this compound, we gain insight into its chemical structure and potential reactivity in various chemical processes.
